page.title: 12OSSETT NATURAL HISTORY
page.content: Ossett town centre is not a very good place to find animals but you will find a lot of insects,e.g.ants,woodlice,beetles etc. A good place to find wild animals is the railway banking.In addition to the normal garden birds you will see Kestrels.The banking also has a lot of flowers.There are mammals such as rabbits,mice,voles,hares and sometimes foxes.You can find many of these animals on Storrs Hill Rocks. There are a lot of footpaths around the banking and surrounding fields,young trees have been planted to encourage wildlife and improve the area. There is a fishing area called Healey Dam in which you find bream,pike,freshwater trout and stickleback.
